# Goose's Ollama stream-stall timeout fires after 30s of no SSE data,
# which kills requests during long silent <thinking> phases of reasoning
# models (qwen3.5, nemotron) with large tool payloads.
#
# In Goose v1.31.1 the only present timeout env var is OLLAMA_TIMEOUT;
# newer versions split it into OLLAMA_STREAM_TIMEOUT / GOOSE_STREAM_TIMEOUT
# (see github.com/block/goose/issues/8437). 300s = 5 min ceiling for
# silent thinking before declaring the model stuck.
#
# Loaded by systemd user sessions — applies to goose-desktop launched
# from the DE and goose CLI in new login shells.
OLLAMA_TIMEOUT=300
